TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Parametric Representation of Additive Value Functions
AU  - Keelin, Thomas W.
Y1  - 1981/10/01
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.27.10.1200
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.27.10.1200
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1200
EP  - 1208
VL  - 27
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper introduces a new parameter for measuring deterministic preference tradeoffs between pairs of attributes. In terms of this parameter, necessary and sufficient conditions for a value function to be additive are established. When additivity conditions are satisfied, a set of these parameters is shown to characterize the value function uniquely up to a set of scaling constants. Implications for assessment, for transforming a nonadditive representation into an additive one, and for multiattribute utility functions are presented.
AB  - This paper introduces a new parameter for measuring deterministic preference tradeoffs between pairs of attributes. In terms of this parameter, necessary and sufficient conditions for a value function to be additive are established. When additivity conditions are satisfied, a set of these parameters is shown to characterize the value function uniquely up to a set of scaling constants. Implications for assessment, for transforming a nonadditive representation into an additive one, and for multiattribute utility functions are presented.
